WEBVTT

00:01.627 --> 00:03.629
[ Water running ]

00:03.629 --> 00:05.631
♪♪

00:05.631 --> 00:07.299
And...tongues.

00:07.299 --> 00:08.926
Both: Ahhhhh.

00:08.926 --> 00:10.052
[ Spits ]
There we are.

00:10.052 --> 00:11.220
They don't teach you that

00:11.220 --> 00:13.597
in special‐needs‐mum school,
do they?

00:13.597 --> 00:14.890
Right.

00:14.890 --> 00:17.017
Aah!
Damn you, narrow door.

00:17.017 --> 00:19.603
You didn't win yesterday.
You're not gonna win today.

00:19.603 --> 00:20.604
Now it's stuck.

00:20.604 --> 00:21.980
Ohh,
I have to pee.

00:21.980 --> 00:23.273
Mom,
I need to get out.

00:23.273 --> 00:24.483
How do we just have
one bathroom?

00:24.483 --> 00:25.901
You're the one
that drinks water

00:25.901 --> 00:27.361
like we're a two‐bathroom
family, Ray.

00:28.445 --> 00:31.114
Dad, how big a drop
out this window?

00:31.114 --> 00:33.700
It'd be fun to find out.

00:33.700 --> 00:35.494
[ Thud ]
About 10 feet!

00:35.494 --> 00:36.703
Good to know.

00:36.703 --> 00:37.955
I need to use
the bathroom.

00:37.955 --> 00:39.623
Go use the one
at the gas station
down the street.

00:39.623 --> 00:41.041
Ooh, and get me lotto tickets
while you're there.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.960
3, 12, 28...
[ Groans ]

00:42.960 --> 00:45.671
Just Quick Pick.
Just get Quick Pick.

00:45.671 --> 00:47.089
[ Water shuts off ]

00:47.089 --> 00:48.549
Darling,
it's really stuck.

00:48.549 --> 00:50.425
I got it.
It's why God gave us soap.

00:51.385 --> 00:53.220
[ Grunts ]

00:53.220 --> 00:54.930
That is really in there,
isn't it?

00:54.930 --> 00:56.306
I'm stuck.

00:56.306 --> 00:58.558
Oh, God.
We're gonna die in here.

00:58.558 --> 00:59.309
Together.

01:04.982 --> 01:07.484
Right.
So, you'll be home by 4:00?

01:07.484 --> 01:08.944
7:00.

01:08.944 --> 01:10.362
You agreed
to eight hours.

01:10.362 --> 01:11.363
That is a long time.

01:11.363 --> 01:12.781
I mean, the longest

01:12.781 --> 01:15.993
JJ's ever been gone
if he wasn't in school is...

01:15.993 --> 01:17.035
How long
is "The Notebook"?

01:17.035 --> 01:19.580
[ Groans ]
Not bloody long enough.

01:19.580 --> 01:22.124
I mean, I love
that Ryan Gosling.

01:22.124 --> 01:26.253
So fast from overprotective
to oversexual.

01:26.253 --> 01:28.046
He can have a day, hon.
He's 16.

01:28.046 --> 01:29.423
All right, just let me see
the to‐do list.

01:29.423 --> 01:30.882
Sorry, no can do.

01:30.882 --> 01:33.677
The deal is eight hours
of total freedom for JJ.

01:33.677 --> 01:36.138
He's driving this, not me,
and definitely not you.

01:36.138 --> 01:37.764
Okay, fine.

01:37.764 --> 01:39.349
But give ‐‐ give ‐‐
give me it!
Oh. Oh.

01:39.349 --> 01:41.476
Seriously, is that as high
as you can jump?

01:41.476 --> 01:42.477
Okay.
Come on.
No. Come on.

01:42.477 --> 01:43.645
Let's get out of here,
JJ.

01:43.645 --> 01:45.188
Let me get you some drinks
for the road.

01:45.188 --> 01:46.315
All right.

01:46.315 --> 01:48.817
Let us see
what is on the agenda here.

01:48.817 --> 01:51.570
"One ‐‐ a whole day
where I call the shots.

01:51.570 --> 01:54.072
Two ‐‐ now, take me to get
hot dogs in L. A., bitch."

01:54.072 --> 01:55.866
‐[ Chuckles ]
‐Oh, you are feisty in lists.

01:55.866 --> 01:56.950
I kind of like it.

01:56.950 --> 01:58.869
Okay, here you go.

01:58.869 --> 02:00.579
Right.
I love you, darling.

02:00.579 --> 02:02.664
‐Have a great time, buddy.
‐Take lots of pictures.

02:02.664 --> 02:04.249
‐Bye, darling.
‐We'll miss you.

02:04.249 --> 02:05.625
I didn't get this
when I went

02:05.625 --> 02:06.835
to go visit Grandma
for a summer.

02:08.587 --> 02:09.796
♪♪

02:09.796 --> 02:12.007
Oh, there he goes.

02:12.007 --> 02:14.301
Yeah.
Just the four of us.

02:14.301 --> 02:17.095
It feels... different.

02:17.095 --> 02:20.599
Should we...do something?

02:20.599 --> 02:22.225
Just us?

02:24.561 --> 02:26.480
[ Snaps fingers ]
I've got it.

02:26.480 --> 02:28.482
‐Besides nap.
‐I'm out.

02:28.482 --> 02:29.566
Let's think.

02:29.566 --> 02:31.777
What is something
we could do as a family

02:31.777 --> 02:36.573
if accessibility
was of absolutely no concern?

02:36.573 --> 02:37.908
Never thought
about that before.

02:37.908 --> 02:39.159
Me neither.

02:39.159 --> 02:40.619
I mean,
I've heard some stuff

02:40.619 --> 02:41.912
other families have done.

02:41.912 --> 02:43.455
I suppose we could...

02:43.455 --> 02:44.956
Rock‐climb?
Parkour?

02:44.956 --> 02:45.957
Mountain bike.
Scuba dive.

02:45.957 --> 02:47.668
Wakeboard.
Windsurf.

02:47.668 --> 02:49.044
Tour a Frank Lloyd Wright
house without ramps.
Kickboxing, skydiving.

02:49.044 --> 02:50.629
Sailing.
Use an escalator.
Chicken fights.
Trapeze classes.

02:50.629 --> 02:51.755
Paintball.
Paintball.

02:51.755 --> 02:53.382
But you've never
thought about it.

02:54.675 --> 02:57.135
You said paintball?
Did we just agree on something?

02:57.135 --> 02:58.470
We never agree.

02:58.470 --> 03:00.347
Don't make it weird, Ray.

03:00.347 --> 03:01.890
You know what your mother might
really enjoy ‐‐ ice skating.

03:01.890 --> 03:03.392
Ugh.

03:03.392 --> 03:05.477
No, your mother was quite
a skater back in her day.

03:05.477 --> 03:07.521
Yeah, yeah, not just parents.
You once had hopes and dreams.

03:07.521 --> 03:08.814
Paintball!

03:08.814 --> 03:10.315
[ Gasps ]
I've got it.

03:10.315 --> 03:12.901
I've got the perfect fun thing
for us to do without JJ.

03:12.901 --> 03:13.985
♪♪

03:13.985 --> 03:15.237
Widen the bathroom door

03:15.237 --> 03:17.072
to make it
wheelchair accessible.

03:19.866 --> 03:20.742
Somebody say something.

03:20.742 --> 03:23.036
I like your hair?

03:23.036 --> 03:24.329
I get it.

03:24.329 --> 03:25.747
You see the fun in my plan,

03:25.747 --> 03:27.040
but you had your heart set
on something else.

03:27.040 --> 03:28.375
Here's what we'll do.

03:28.375 --> 03:30.127
I'll go and gather
a few supplies.

03:30.127 --> 03:31.837
You guys knock out the wall.

03:31.837 --> 03:33.630
We fix the door fast,
then on to paintball.

03:33.630 --> 03:34.965
Is that even possible?

03:34.965 --> 03:36.216
With my dream team it is.

03:36.216 --> 03:38.927
You're the brains.
You're the brawn.

03:38.927 --> 03:42.973
And you're the big, strong man
who actually knows how to do it.

03:42.973 --> 03:44.099
I am handy.

03:46.184 --> 03:47.519
But you're gonna let him
use the bat?

03:47.519 --> 03:48.854
I know what I'm doing.

03:51.398 --> 03:53.191
Congratulations, toaster.

03:53.191 --> 03:55.652
You are now
our most valuable possession.

03:55.652 --> 03:58.029
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:58.029 --> 04:01.491
[ Sighs ] JJ, we've got one day
to do whatever you want.

04:01.491 --> 04:05.203
You sure you want to spend it
in this line?

04:05.203 --> 04:07.456
G‐U‐Y‐F ‐‐

04:07.456 --> 04:09.499
Yes, I understand
Guy Fieri likes it.

04:09.499 --> 04:11.209
Still...

04:11.209 --> 04:12.711
Man,
you've got like no pores.

04:12.711 --> 04:14.296
Respect.

04:14.296 --> 04:16.506
You two sweeties
shouldn't have to wait in line.

04:16.506 --> 04:17.674
Come with me.

04:17.674 --> 04:20.218
Okay.

04:20.218 --> 04:22.012
Excuse me. We have a couple
of V. I. P. s here.

04:22.012 --> 04:23.597
Uh, thank you.

04:23.597 --> 04:25.474
Another day,
another old white lady thinks

04:25.474 --> 04:27.267
I'm some doctor
from "Grey's Anatomy."

04:27.267 --> 04:29.644
Two chili dogs
for me and my friend, please.

04:29.644 --> 04:32.564
You know what?
Um, lunch is on us.

04:32.564 --> 04:34.107
‐Really?
‐Yeah.

04:34.107 --> 04:36.526
Thanks.
[ Chuckles ]

04:36.526 --> 04:37.944
You always get treated
like this?

04:38.612 --> 04:40.697
Yeah, me neither.

04:40.697 --> 04:43.492
The only special attention I get
is when I'm driving home

04:43.492 --> 04:46.161
and Waze accidentally leads me
through the nice neighborhood.

04:46.161 --> 04:48.872
Um, excuse me,
I got to ask.

04:48.872 --> 04:50.582
Is no one upset
that we cut the line?

04:50.582 --> 04:51.958
Not at all.

04:51.958 --> 04:53.543
Uh‐huh.
It's 'cause of the kid, right?

04:53.543 --> 04:54.753
And you.

04:54.753 --> 04:57.088
I mean, you're this big,
manly guy,

04:57.088 --> 04:58.715
but you're treating him
with such tenderness.

04:58.715 --> 05:00.467
It's heartwarming.

05:00.467 --> 05:02.469
Oh, well,
I could see that ‐‐

05:02.469 --> 05:05.305
cute kid and gentle giant
sort of thing.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.808
And I find myself asking,
who's helping who?

05:07.808 --> 05:08.934
Does that make sense?

05:08.934 --> 05:10.101
Yeah, totally.

05:10.101 --> 05:11.102
‐Of course.
‐That.

05:11.102 --> 05:12.395
‐Yeah.
‐Yeah.

05:12.395 --> 05:13.480
Hmm.

05:14.689 --> 05:18.777
Might this extend to other
non‐hot‐dog situations?

05:18.777 --> 05:22.989
JJ, we are pushing this
as far as we can.

05:22.989 --> 05:25.450
"Pushing what?"
What?

05:25.450 --> 05:28.787
[ Whispering ]
JJ, we're inspirations!

05:28.787 --> 05:31.164
[ Applause ]

05:31.164 --> 05:33.333
Thank you, guys.
Thank you.

05:34.668 --> 05:36.586
It comes right out.
[ Grunts ]

05:36.586 --> 05:38.672
Just like picking a scab.

05:39.881 --> 05:41.091
Unless you're weak.

05:41.091 --> 05:42.259
I'm not weak.

05:42.259 --> 05:44.052
I just got
this sucky hammer.

05:48.265 --> 05:49.516
[ Board clatters ]

05:49.516 --> 05:50.767
I fixed your hammer.

05:50.767 --> 05:52.185
Is there any way

05:52.185 --> 05:53.687
we can finish this
in time for paintball?

05:53.687 --> 05:55.105
I don't know.

05:55.105 --> 05:57.649
Mom seemed
so sure we could.

05:57.649 --> 05:59.818
Hey, Dad, after we're done
fixing this doorjamb,

05:59.818 --> 06:01.152
how much work is left?

06:01.152 --> 06:02.946
Well, God,
I mean, after that,

06:02.946 --> 06:05.490
we need to, uh ‐‐
we ‐‐ we should probably, uh...

06:05.490 --> 06:06.783
Wait a second.

06:06.783 --> 06:09.077
I don't know how to do this.
I'm not handy!

06:09.077 --> 06:10.120
She did it again.
Ha!

06:10.120 --> 06:11.663
‐Did what?
‐Your mom.

06:11.663 --> 06:14.249
She gets all charming
and flattery and British,

06:14.249 --> 06:16.459
and the next thing you know,
you think you're a contractor.

06:16.459 --> 06:19.546
Or an accountant. I'm not
qualified to do our taxes.

06:19.546 --> 06:23.091
[ Sighs ] She never wanted
to go to paintball.

06:23.091 --> 06:25.760
Enjoying an activity
JJ couldn't participate in

06:25.760 --> 06:27.804
would play too much into her
deep‐seated issues of guilt.

06:28.847 --> 06:30.140
How do I know this?

06:30.140 --> 06:31.808
She made me read
a psychology textbook

06:31.808 --> 06:34.311
to give her free therapy.

06:34.311 --> 06:36.313
[ Sighs ] I can't believe
we fell for this.

06:36.313 --> 06:38.857
No. No.
Don't beat yourself up.

06:38.857 --> 06:41.651
When Mom turns on the charm,
no one is immune.

06:41.651 --> 06:42.694
Hello.

06:42.694 --> 06:46.406
Might it be fun
to loan me your saw?

06:46.406 --> 06:47.490
I'm not gonna lie.

06:47.490 --> 06:49.618
That ‐‐ That does sound
pretty fun.

06:49.618 --> 06:50.910
Announcer:
<i>Attention, Dodger fans.</i>
Woman: Thank you.

06:50.910 --> 06:53.413
<i>Next week is Dodgers</i>
<i>Family Day.</i>
Thank you.

06:53.413 --> 06:54.497
Why, hello, there.

06:54.497 --> 06:55.957
Uh,
the line's back there.

06:55.957 --> 06:57.792
Um, that's okay,

06:57.792 --> 07:00.420
uh, 'cause we don't have tickets
to give you, anyway.

07:01.421 --> 07:03.882
♪♪

07:03.882 --> 07:05.884
Welcome to Dodger Stadium.

07:05.884 --> 07:07.427
[ Laughs ]

07:07.427 --> 07:09.679
Thank you.

07:09.679 --> 07:11.723
Good news!
Found a saw.

07:11.723 --> 07:13.516
Oh, way ahead of you.
We're finished.

07:13.516 --> 07:15.560
‐Finished?
‐Yeah.

07:15.560 --> 07:19.147
We widened the doors,
smoothed off the edges.

07:19.147 --> 07:21.608
A little brain, some brawn ‐‐
there's nothing you can't do.

07:21.608 --> 07:22.901
Mm?

07:22.901 --> 07:23.902
Let me see that chair.

07:23.902 --> 07:25.278
Oh,
there'll be plenty of time

07:25.278 --> 07:26.821
for the examination
of chairs and such
after paintball.

07:26.821 --> 07:28.156
Ah.

07:30.116 --> 07:33.203
That's not where my hands go.
<i>That's</i> where my hands go.

07:33.203 --> 07:36.122
You didn't widen the door.
You narrowed the chair.

07:36.122 --> 07:37.666
You're tricking me.
Well, you tricked me first

07:37.666 --> 07:39.084
by making me believe
I'm not incompetent.

07:39.084 --> 07:40.460
Damn your charm.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.337
Is it fun
to give her our saw?

07:42.337 --> 07:44.547
Fine. I used my powers to make
you think you were able.

07:44.547 --> 07:46.424
I apologize.

07:46.424 --> 07:49.052
You go and paintball.
I'll finish the door.

07:49.052 --> 07:50.512
I mean it.
Have fun.

07:50.512 --> 07:52.430
♪♪

07:52.430 --> 07:55.558
Could we first take a moment
to examine your choice?

07:55.558 --> 07:58.103
Are you, Maya,
avoiding paintball

07:58.103 --> 08:00.605
because you feel guilty
for enjoying an activity

08:00.605 --> 08:03.024
in which your son
could not participate?

08:03.024 --> 08:04.984
I mean,
perhaps on some level, yeah.

08:04.984 --> 08:06.986
And what are
the two kinds of guilt?

08:06.986 --> 08:11.157
Healthy/appropriate
and unhealthy/inappropriate.

08:11.157 --> 08:12.992
See, JJ is having fun,

08:12.992 --> 08:16.037
so any guilt related
to his experience must be...

08:16.037 --> 08:17.205
Unhealthy.

08:17.205 --> 08:18.289
That's right.

08:18.289 --> 08:20.417
And when we let
our actions be dictated

08:20.417 --> 08:22.377
by unhealthy guilt,
we...

08:22.377 --> 08:24.796
Choose a course that causes
true harm, right?

08:24.796 --> 08:26.798
Yes.
Just like my mother!

08:26.798 --> 08:28.174
All right, screw it.

08:28.174 --> 08:29.509
Let's go and do paintball,
shall we?

08:29.509 --> 08:31.136
Come on.

08:32.554 --> 08:34.472
That's all the time
we have for today.

08:38.268 --> 08:39.602
‐Do these seats work?
‐Yeah.

08:39.602 --> 08:40.937
Nice view...

08:40.937 --> 08:43.481
from those great seats
down there.

08:45.775 --> 08:47.652
♪♪

08:47.652 --> 08:49.446
Whoa!

08:49.446 --> 08:52.615
Yeah, man.
This'll do.

08:52.615 --> 08:54.284
Uh, any movement
on our other request?

08:54.284 --> 08:56.077
I'm afraid
it's gonna be impossible.

08:56.077 --> 08:57.746
Yeah, we get it.
Yeah.

08:57.746 --> 08:59.080
Some things
just can't be done.

09:02.208 --> 09:04.169
Announcer:
<i>Please welcome to the field</i>

09:04.169 --> 09:06.129
<i>to throw out the first pitch,</i>

09:06.129 --> 09:10.216
<i>JJ DiMeo and Kenneth!</i>

09:10.216 --> 09:12.719
We sound like
a ventriloquist act.

09:14.679 --> 09:16.681
"We kinda are."

09:16.681 --> 09:19.642
Yeah.

09:19.642 --> 09:22.020
[ Organ playing ]

09:22.020 --> 09:26.441
[ Cheers and applause ]

09:26.441 --> 09:29.277
[ Laughs ] Yeah.

09:29.277 --> 09:31.863
[ Noisemakers rattling ]

09:33.698 --> 09:35.075
"And the glove."

09:36.618 --> 09:39.829
♪♪

09:39.829 --> 09:41.498
Yeah! Right? Yeah!

09:41.498 --> 09:44.042
Look at this place.

09:44.042 --> 09:45.877
The grade, the terrain.

09:45.877 --> 09:47.253
We're gonna have the most

09:47.253 --> 09:50.090
wheelchair‐inaccessible
day ever.

09:57.514 --> 09:58.973
10,000 hours of "Halo."

09:58.973 --> 10:00.975
Wait.

10:00.975 --> 10:02.435
Are you awesome?

10:02.435 --> 10:04.354
Wait.

10:04.354 --> 10:05.897
Are you nice?

10:05.897 --> 10:07.315
Maya: Oh,
this is gonna be such fun.

10:07.315 --> 10:10.401
The clothes, the violence ‐‐
fantastic.

10:10.401 --> 10:12.403
I can't believe
you're this into it.

10:12.403 --> 10:15.198
And yet you do believe.
That's how good I am.

10:15.198 --> 10:17.242
Right, kids,
DiMeo's the name,

10:17.242 --> 10:18.993
murder's the game.

10:18.993 --> 10:20.662
Big American gun party.

10:20.662 --> 10:22.122
No mercy, right?

10:22.122 --> 10:24.457
Announcer:
<i>Play commences in three, two...</i>

10:24.457 --> 10:25.959
You three go on ahead.

10:25.959 --> 10:26.960
I've got your back.
[ Buzzer ]

10:26.960 --> 10:28.044
Where will you be?

10:28.044 --> 10:29.587
The perfect spot.

10:31.214 --> 10:33.550
♪♪

10:35.635 --> 10:38.179
This looks like
a good napping spot.

10:38.179 --> 10:41.224
[ Sighs ]
Good night, paintball.

10:41.224 --> 10:44.644
[ Laughs ]
I never get to do this.

10:44.644 --> 10:46.813
Ready?

10:46.813 --> 10:49.482
"Enough of that.

10:49.482 --> 10:52.193
We're here
to watch the game."

10:53.570 --> 10:56.739
Civilians watch the game.
We're inspirations.

10:56.739 --> 10:58.241
All right.

10:58.241 --> 11:00.034
Announcer:
<i>It's Kiss Cam time!</i>
Mmmmm.

11:00.034 --> 11:02.412
Come on, man.
Give it to them.

11:02.412 --> 11:03.746
Give them the kiss.

11:03.746 --> 11:06.124
Give them a little ‐‐
mwah ‐‐ lips.

11:06.124 --> 11:07.959
Give it to them, man.

11:07.959 --> 11:09.878
Yeah!
[ Laughs ]

11:09.878 --> 11:11.171
All right.

11:11.171 --> 11:13.673
Now we can just watch
the game, okay?

11:13.673 --> 11:15.091
All right.

11:15.091 --> 11:17.677
Crowd: ♪ If they don't win,
it's a shame ♪

11:17.677 --> 11:19.554
♪ For it's one ♪

11:19.554 --> 11:20.805
Crowd: ♪ Two ♪

11:20.805 --> 11:22.307
♪ Three strikes, you're out ♪

11:22.307 --> 11:27.770
♪ At the old ballgame ♪

11:27.770 --> 11:29.606
[ Laughs ]

11:29.606 --> 11:31.649
[ Applause ]

11:32.901 --> 11:34.611
[ Paintball guns popping ]

11:34.611 --> 11:36.487
10:00!

11:36.487 --> 11:37.864
2:00!

11:39.908 --> 11:41.492
[ Breathing heavily ]

11:41.492 --> 11:42.744
I love killing people
with you.

11:42.744 --> 11:44.370
I love everything
about you.

11:44.370 --> 11:45.622
How did we not know
about this until now?

11:45.622 --> 11:46.998
Maybe 'cause it's never
just the two of us.

11:46.998 --> 11:48.917
[ Paintball thuds ]
Take cover!

11:48.917 --> 11:51.002
♪♪

11:51.002 --> 11:53.087
[ Paintball guns popping ]

11:53.087 --> 11:55.298
Oi!

11:55.298 --> 11:56.925
Special‐needs‐mum
phone check time out.

11:56.925 --> 11:59.385
There is no time out.

11:59.385 --> 12:00.470
Ow!

12:00.470 --> 12:01.596
[ Laughs ]

12:01.596 --> 12:02.430
Bloody little...

12:02.430 --> 12:04.265
Right.

12:04.265 --> 12:05.642
Ohh!

12:05.642 --> 12:06.809
Jimmy?

12:06.809 --> 12:09.229
I'm up.
I'm up.

12:09.229 --> 12:10.313
Those monsters!

12:10.313 --> 12:11.773
They shot you
in my favorite breast!

12:11.773 --> 12:13.733
Oh, come on!

12:13.733 --> 12:15.485
[ Sighs ]

12:15.485 --> 12:17.779
Why are we
still doing this?

12:19.322 --> 12:20.823
Let's get out of here.

12:20.823 --> 12:24.494
[ Paintball guns popping ]

12:24.494 --> 12:25.453
There's too many of them.

12:25.453 --> 12:26.913
We can't hold them off
much longer.

12:26.913 --> 12:28.081
Not today they're not.

12:29.916 --> 12:30.833
Did that not link?
I'm sorry.

12:30.833 --> 12:32.460
I didn't really hear
what you said.
[ Paintball whizzes ]

12:32.460 --> 12:33.836
Ohh!

12:33.836 --> 12:35.713
Hey, we're surrounded!
Circle up!

12:35.713 --> 12:39.133
♪♪

12:43.763 --> 12:44.931
It's working.

12:45.932 --> 12:47.809
They're backing off.

12:47.809 --> 12:49.018
[ Paintball gun clicks ]

12:49.018 --> 12:50.520
My gun's jammed.

12:51.604 --> 12:52.730
Oh, crap.

12:52.730 --> 13:00.488
Nooooooooooo!

13:02.490 --> 13:05.076
♪♪

13:05.868 --> 13:08.079
[ Grunting ]

13:13.543 --> 13:15.336
[ Laughs ]

13:16.421 --> 13:18.006
‐No hits.
‐Hey.

13:18.006 --> 13:20.466
Me neither.
Ha!

13:20.466 --> 13:22.552
The DiMeos rule!

13:22.552 --> 13:25.221
This is the best day ever!
[ Gasps ]

13:29.309 --> 13:32.562
I mean...I miss JJ?

13:32.562 --> 13:34.355
What a day!
[ Laughs ]

13:34.355 --> 13:36.774
Look at all these programs
I got.

13:36.774 --> 13:38.151
I don't want these.

13:39.736 --> 13:41.529
Uh,
up for one more stop?

13:42.989 --> 13:44.824
E‐N ‐‐ "Enough."

13:44.824 --> 13:48.745
Well, enough energy
to go to the Stones concert?

13:48.745 --> 13:49.704
Yeah, man.

13:49.704 --> 13:51.706
Whoo!

13:51.706 --> 13:54.333
Oh, one last inspirational
score of the day.

13:54.333 --> 13:56.127
Guess what we don't have ‐‐
tickets.

13:56.127 --> 13:58.296
Guess what we don't need ‐‐
tickets.

13:58.296 --> 14:00.214
[ Laughs ]
Whoo.

14:00.214 --> 14:01.716
[ Door opens ]
Yoo! [ Laughs ]

14:01.716 --> 14:03.760
Yeah, man.
[ Door closes ]

14:03.760 --> 14:06.220
All right.
Let's get in the mood.

14:06.220 --> 14:08.181
What's your favorite
Stones song?

14:08.181 --> 14:10.224
[ Laughs ]
I don't have any Stones.

14:10.224 --> 14:11.976
My cousin's band it is.

14:11.976 --> 14:12.977
[ Funky music playing ]

14:12.977 --> 14:14.687
You like this, right?
[ Chuckles ]

14:14.687 --> 14:17.231
Rodney, he likes it.

14:17.231 --> 14:18.483
Rodney's dead.

14:18.483 --> 14:21.486
♪♪

14:23.237 --> 14:25.281
It's not the best day ever.
I didn't mean it.

14:25.281 --> 14:26.741
We know you didn't,
sweetheart.

14:26.741 --> 14:28.659
Except I did, which makes me
a terrible person.

14:28.659 --> 14:30.203
Why didn't
we just fix the door?

14:30.203 --> 14:32.663
What's wrong with making life
a little easier for JJ?

14:32.663 --> 14:34.499
Exactly, it's like he deals
with so much,

14:34.499 --> 14:35.625
and he doesn't complain.

14:35.625 --> 14:36.834
All I do is complain.

14:36.834 --> 14:38.336
[ Paint splattering ]
You think about that, too?

14:38.336 --> 14:39.754
That's all I think.

14:39.754 --> 14:40.797
You guys feel guilty?

14:40.797 --> 14:42.423
You have nothing
to feel guilty about.

14:42.423 --> 14:44.926
Don't go wide.
It's one day.

14:44.926 --> 14:46.427
You can have fun
without your brother.

14:46.427 --> 14:48.262
[ Paint splatters ]
Son of a ‐‐
Yeah, right.

14:48.262 --> 14:49.430
‐What does that mean?
‐Mom never does.

14:49.430 --> 14:51.224
[ Paint splatters ]

14:51.224 --> 14:53.559
Oh, my God.
This is all my fault.

14:53.559 --> 14:54.769
[ Paint splatters ]
Ow!
Ow.
Ohh.

14:54.769 --> 14:57.480
Oh, please, kids.
Don't feel ‐‐ Ow ‐‐ guilty.

14:57.480 --> 14:59.232
Ow!
Ow!
Ow!

14:59.232 --> 15:02.944
This is the worst day
ever!!

15:07.532 --> 15:09.325
Hee! The Dodgers and the Stones
all in one day.

15:09.325 --> 15:10.535
[ Laughs ]
This is gonna be great.

15:10.535 --> 15:12.537
Let's practice our smiles.

15:14.413 --> 15:16.624
Yours doesn't look so good.
What's wrong?

15:16.624 --> 15:18.251
Let's get your board.

15:18.251 --> 15:19.961
It's in the backpack,
but where's that?

15:19.961 --> 15:21.546
[ Sighs ]

15:21.546 --> 15:22.964
What ‐‐

15:22.964 --> 15:24.757
<i>I</i> left it someplace?

15:24.757 --> 15:25.883
Okay, uh...

15:25.883 --> 15:27.510
[ Sighs ]
We can fix this.

15:27.510 --> 15:29.428
Uh...

15:29.428 --> 15:30.847
Okay, JJ,
I'll give you some options.

15:30.847 --> 15:32.306
We left it at the stadium.

15:32.306 --> 15:33.766
Do we have to check
the whole place

15:33.766 --> 15:34.559
or did you see it?

15:35.726 --> 15:37.228
Okay.
Um, good.

15:37.228 --> 15:39.397
Was it in the parking lot
or before that?

15:39.397 --> 15:40.690
Okay, great.

15:40.690 --> 15:42.066
We'll go back
to the parking lot.

15:42.066 --> 15:43.568
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

15:43.568 --> 15:46.279
Look at us, thinking of a way
to make it work.

15:46.279 --> 15:48.197
Impressive thinking
on the fly

15:48.197 --> 15:50.074
or wrong time
to do a victory lap?

15:51.701 --> 15:54.871
Okay, stop yelling at me.
I got it.

15:54.871 --> 15:57.498
♪♪

15:57.498 --> 15:59.125
How are the kids?

15:59.125 --> 16:01.252
I hosed them off.
They're fine.

16:01.252 --> 16:03.921
I can't believe they think
I don't have any fun.

16:05.089 --> 16:06.757
What?
You agree with them?

16:06.757 --> 16:08.217
I'm just saying.
Name one thing.

16:09.927 --> 16:12.847
Well,
there's... um...

16:12.847 --> 16:14.557
Um...

16:17.018 --> 16:18.895
I lit a candle
a few months ago.

16:18.895 --> 16:21.772
Hon...

16:21.772 --> 16:24.025
it's time for you to
do something selfish
for once in your life.

16:24.025 --> 16:28.362
The kids need to see you
having fun just for you,

16:28.362 --> 16:30.781
something bigger than, you know,
lighting a candle.

16:32.366 --> 16:35.494
Yeah, I didn't really
light a candle.

16:35.494 --> 16:37.496
Wow.
You guys sure make a cute team.

16:37.496 --> 16:39.165
You know,
you're real inspir‐‐

16:39.165 --> 16:40.750
Yeah,
we're done with that.

16:40.750 --> 16:42.001
[ Zipper opens ]

16:45.379 --> 16:48.090
All right, buddy.
Let me have it.

16:48.090 --> 16:50.343
"I'm mad."

16:50.343 --> 16:52.887
Well, I‐I got that
without the board.

16:52.887 --> 16:58.476
"Today was about what I ‐‐
W‐A ‐‐ wanted.

16:58.476 --> 17:02.230
You took
my ‐‐ V‐O ‐‐ voice.

17:02.230 --> 17:04.440
You...

17:04.440 --> 17:08.736
don't get
to do that."

17:08.736 --> 17:10.780
[ Sighs ]

17:12.448 --> 17:16.035
JJ, I am so, so sorry.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.620
I'm not used
to special treatment,

17:17.620 --> 17:20.206
and it went to my head.

17:20.206 --> 17:24.335
But I promise you it will
never happen again, ever.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.132
You know what?

17:30.132 --> 17:32.176
Maybe something
can be salvaged here.

17:32.176 --> 17:36.138
No inspirations.
All you.

17:37.807 --> 17:39.725
I promised you
a day of independence.

17:39.725 --> 17:40.977
You wanted to drive it.

17:40.977 --> 17:42.812
Drive this.

17:42.812 --> 17:45.565
All right.

17:45.565 --> 17:48.776
Parking lot is empty,
and this van already looks

17:48.776 --> 17:50.695
like it's been wrapped
around a pole.
[ Chuckles ]

17:50.695 --> 17:53.698
Don't wrap it around a pole,
all right?

17:53.698 --> 17:55.408
Uh...

17:55.408 --> 17:57.201
[ Engine starts ]

17:58.661 --> 18:01.581
All right, just give it
a little bit of gas!

18:01.581 --> 18:02.540
Whoa!

18:02.540 --> 18:03.666
Oh, oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh!

18:03.666 --> 18:05.334
Oh!
JJ.

18:05.334 --> 18:07.086
Aah!
Aah!

18:09.130 --> 18:10.548
Happy Independence Day!

18:10.548 --> 18:12.717
[ Laughs ]

18:12.717 --> 18:14.927
Whoo!
Oh.

18:14.927 --> 18:16.512
Aah!

18:16.512 --> 18:19.307
I'm coming to meet you,
Rodney!

18:19.307 --> 18:20.141
Whoo!

18:22.351 --> 18:24.312
[ Soft music plays ]

18:24.312 --> 18:25.813
I'm really not feeling it.

18:25.813 --> 18:27.732
I mean,
so they'll be ruled by guilt.

18:27.732 --> 18:29.525
It's fine.

18:29.525 --> 18:34.030
Maya,
we paid $3 for this.

18:34.030 --> 18:35.323
You're doing it.

18:36.282 --> 18:37.491
Come on.
Fake it till you make it.

18:37.491 --> 18:39.285
[ Sighs ]

18:45.625 --> 18:47.627
♪♪

18:50.838 --> 18:53.382
Look at that.
Your mom <i>can</i> have fun.

18:53.382 --> 18:56.761
She's not feeling guilty.
Neither should you.

18:56.761 --> 18:58.054
[ Blades scratching ]

19:00.348 --> 19:01.599
You guys want
to join her?

19:01.599 --> 19:03.267
No, I'm pretty happy
right here.

19:03.267 --> 19:04.310
Me too.

19:07.229 --> 19:09.065
Ow!
[Bleep]

19:09.065 --> 19:11.067
Son of a [bleep]

19:11.067 --> 19:13.653
Ow!

19:13.653 --> 19:16.405
I broke my ass.

19:16.405 --> 19:18.658
She proved her point
before this, right?

19:18.658 --> 19:20.159
Yeah.
Yeah.
Okay.

19:22.620 --> 19:25.373
Hey!
The DiMeos are home!

19:25.373 --> 19:28.000
I want to be clear.
I did not do this.

19:29.210 --> 19:30.419
Hello, darling.

19:30.419 --> 19:31.629
[ Door closes ]

19:31.629 --> 19:33.923
Oh, I missed you
so much.

19:33.923 --> 19:36.384
Oh, it was no fun without you.
I was miserable.

19:36.384 --> 19:38.260
Eh, we didn't do
anything that cool.

19:38.260 --> 19:40.221
At no point
was I having a blast.

19:40.221 --> 19:41.347
Kenneth: Yeah,
how about you, buddy?

19:41.347 --> 19:42.723
What was the most independent
thing you did today?

19:42.723 --> 19:45.685
"Drove a car."

19:45.685 --> 19:48.479
[ Laughter ]

19:50.648 --> 19:53.025
♪♪

19:53.025 --> 19:54.985
Wait.
For real?

19:56.946 --> 19:59.115
Kenneth, what ‐‐

20:03.411 --> 20:06.163
[ Water running ]

20:06.163 --> 20:07.415
Ray?

20:07.415 --> 20:09.583
Ray: I'm in here.
Did you not see the sign?

20:09.583 --> 20:10.793
I did.

20:10.793 --> 20:12.461
And it all
came rushing back.

20:12.461 --> 20:14.004
What did?
How much I love
torturing you.

20:15.297 --> 20:17.883
Aah!
Aah!

20:17.883 --> 20:19.301
I thought
we were a team!

20:19.301 --> 20:21.846
We were.
It was great.

20:21.846 --> 20:23.681
This is just more fun.

20:23.681 --> 20:25.599
Aah!
Aah!

20:25.599 --> 20:26.767
Aah!

20:26.767 --> 20:28.227
Ohh, no!

20:28.227 --> 20:29.228
Ray?

20:29.228 --> 20:30.855
What?!

20:30.855 --> 20:33.023
We'll always have
paintball.
